Original_notes: 6 yr. cycles: cultivated 1 yr. in [6?]. Small trees, suitable for fencemaking, grow in this period; but this secondary growth is sharply distinguished from virgin rainforest, none of which has been cleared within memory
plant rubbish burned and scattered over garden to enrich it
(+); fences [underlined]; primarily, I think, as protection against pigs, might also delimit property

(+); which unit?; "Aboriginal settlements consist of small, one- to nine-house hamlets scattered about the scrub." Houses were for nuclear families; But "neighborhoods" - which may include hostile factions and the elements of which do not commonly co-operate - may have from 6 to 50 households. In these a minimal bond of co-residence is recognized, and free right of way given
built by rival native "leaders" at instigation of the Australian authorities
only Ho≈ãing, among a large class of primal beings, remains active as a "universal" agent; and he is not worshipped
